  "body": "Like the documentation for our `set_var` (setenv) says, care must be taken with mutating environment variables in a multithreaded program. See [this glibc bug #13271](https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=13271) that says getaddrinfo may call getenv.\n\nIt looks like we have an unsynchronized call to getaddrinfo and this may cause trouble with glibc/Linux.\n\nSeeing glibc's attitude to setenv in multithreaded programs, `set_var` seems like a big hazard in general(?).\n\nDiscovered as an issue tangential to #27966\n\ncc @alexcrichton \n",
